\section*{3.DISTRIBUTIVE SHOCK :}

Occurs due to abnormal distribution of blood flow .This type is further divided into three subtypes .They include :

 SEPTIC SHOCK:
It is induced by severe bacterial infections or septicemia. It may result from either gram negative or gram positive bacteria which release toxins which results to activation of macrophages and monocytes and vasodilation leading to hypotension and decrease in tissue perfusion.

